Subject:Re: [EVDL] EVLN: Focus guessometer-overreaction,
	too-much info for noob-driver
Luckily a lot of the members of public also recognise
that they are being lied to by (paid) media, so the old method
of spreading news via your circle of friends still is one of the
strongest influencers. Just like the "expert" once proclaiming that
no computer user ever needed more than 64kB was swept aside by
early adopters who were running nice games and other programs
in expanded memory and showed their friends, who recognised it as
desirable and not be limited by the "expert" statement.

Adjustable levels of sophisticated display is not so much to
limit the distraction - many drivers will allow far too much
distraction to drive safely and concentrated anyway, but to
make it usable / understandable to the inexperienced users.
I have regularly seen TV remotes with a blank paper taped across
and only cutouts to show the up/down and standby buttons.
All the other buttons are hidden because they are too confusing....

The electronic EV version of this is what Bruce described.

Cor van de Water
